<TITLE> 10 hurt in Feni train-truck collision </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Feni, July 23 (bdnews24.com)  Ten people including four railway employees were injured early Thursday when a passenger train rammed into a loaded truck stuck at the Fatehpur level crossing on the Dhaka-Chittagong highway in Feni. Rail communication between Feni and the rest of the country has been snapped since the accident. Feni assistant railway station master Mohammed Harun told bdnews24.com the engine of the iron coil carrying truck stopped while negotiating the level crossing at around 5am and the Chittagong-bound passenger train Turna-Nishitha hit the standing truck, causing three of its compartments to derail. The driver and the helpers of the truck fled the scene. The injured were admitted to local clinics, Harun said. A relief train arrived at the spot from Chittagong at around 9 am. A police team led by ASP Headquarters Shakila Sultana is overseeing the rescue operation, the railway official said. bdnews
